<item>
            <title>[LU-12086] Add get_lustre_env to all test scripts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12086</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As seen in:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34285/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34285/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Developers are starting to assume these variables are available everywhere, but that&apos;s not yet the case.&#160; In that example, get_lustre_env is not called in replay-single.sh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We eventually want to convert old tests to using these, but that&apos;s a slightly herculean task and we&apos;re introducing bugs today by not having these available.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So let&apos;s the get_lustre_env call to all of our test scripts.&#160; (I looked for every place we called &quot;init_logging&quot; and added the env call next to it.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
